				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "## What is an SSDLC?"
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [ ]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-08-18T20:41:58.06441-05:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-08-18T20:42:36.43149-05:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "W53fsg/5DQC1gHUjB+THzQ=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "Honestly, it’s a pretty fuzzy concept. Any sort of description of your development process and how you embed security into the steps qualifies in my book, but then again, I’m not an auditor."
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [ ]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-08-18T20:56:59.038937-05:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-08-18T20:59:31.084838-05:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "sYyp4w/5DQC5A6+dB+THzQ=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "You can go down the rabbit hole and look at the [NIST SSDF](https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/218/final) or [OWASP SAMM](https://owaspsamm.org/). It will get you there, and you’ll honestly be better off than just following my scrappy Markdown doc above. But I would argue that it’s also much more heavyweight than what most small teams actually benefit from, and you can get most of the benefit just by caring, writing down your intentions, and building some automated guardrails."
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [ ]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-08-18T20:59:33.014056-05:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-08-18T21:28:52.381566-05:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "kd3A8Q/5DQCAPL1VB+THzQ=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "Now, to have an SSDLC that works, you will definitely, undoubtedly, unquestionably need a threat model. If you don’t have a threat model, you do not know what you are defending against. You do not know what is in scope. Are you defending against automated portscans or the Mossad spiking your CIO’s drink to get to his laptop? These are fairly different scenarios. Call me when you need help with the first, and someone else when you need the second (but do tell me your stories)."
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [ ]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-08-18T21:02:05.644273-05:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-08-18T21:29:00.192012-05:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "59HZ+g/5DQCI7JeZB+THzQ=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "Once you have a threat model, you can derive some system properties from it. Many will not change from project to project. Use strong standard cryptography. Do as little of your RBAC yourself as you can. Restrict root access to production systems. Log, alert, monitor."
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [ ]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-08-18T21:05:29.387656-05:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-08-18T21:05:29.387656-05:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "wbL+BhD5DQCSVfUsB+THzQ=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "Other things will be bespoke to your project, like user roles, how tenants are separated, things like that. They are informed by your threat model, but you will still have to think about them."
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [ ]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-08-18T21:04:00.178352-05:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-08-18T21:36:14.691762-05:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "+HitARD5DQCNlsZZB+THzQ=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "As part of your SSDLC, you will also think about the implications of any change to that threat model and your security assumptions, and about the risks you introduce, mitigate, defer, or accept. It should help you formalize a process of continuously monitoring the boundaries of your system and whether the assumptions your team made still hold."
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [ ]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-08-18T21:07:29.193257-05:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-08-18T21:13:52.522353-05:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "VcgiDhD5DQCXoSvLB+THzQ=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "## How to introduce an SSDLC?"
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [ ]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-08-18T21:13:55.282112-05:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-08-18T21:15:23.630395-05:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "wwkmJRD5DQCYmkTSB+THzQ=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "Assuming you already have a threat model, you can adopt a simple SSDLC in two to three weeks (or sprints, or cycles, or whatever your prefereed unit of measurement is). Let me try to formalize it, but do adjust to your needs:"
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [ ]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-08-18T21:15:34.015034-05:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-08-18T21:33:29.220645-05:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "nVatKhD5DQCcpIGfB+THzQ=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "Phase 1: Add security implications and threat model delta to issue/user story template and MR/PR template; define your list of approved cryptography (defer to an authority like BSI or NIST if possible).\nPhase 2: Add your CI steps to generate an SBOM and sign your artifacts ([read my post](/Some_notes_about_SBOMs.html)); pin your base images (by digest) and whatever else can be pinned. Add as many CI automations as possible ([syft](https://github.com/anchore/syft), [trivy](https://trivy.dev/latest/), [gitleaks](https://github.com/gitleaks/gitleaks), [semgrep](https://semgrep.dev/), [renovate](https://github.com/renovatebot/renovate), [cosign](https://github.com/sigstore/cosign), etc.), but not more than you will actually use and maintain, noone likes looking at stale Dependabot alerts.\nPhase 3: Turn on CI; add a few smoke tests (covering, for instance, log redaction)."
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [ ]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-08-18T21:20:45.80422-05:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2025-08-18T21:29:12.00799-05:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "tBqePRD5DQCpDgpyB+THzQ=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "What I wouldn’t include from the get-go includes everything from super heavyweight docs, manual gates, or bespoke “seucrity reviews”. If it can’t be automated or proven, it probably won’t happen unless an auditor is looking<sup><a href=\"#1\">1</a></sup>."
			},
